Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%oz} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces.
Peel and cut @onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.
Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons.

> Pat chicken dry with paper towels before cooking.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{}
over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe
out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add carrots, onion, and zucchini; season with @garlic powder{1%tsp},
@Italian seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until veggies are softened and lightly browned, ~{7-10%minutes}.

Add @crushed tomatoes{13.76%oz}, 1⁄4 cup water, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until sauce has slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

== Polenta ==

Meanwhile, heat a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add @precooked polenta{8.8%oz}
and 1/3 cup water. Mash with a #potato masher{} until mostly smooth,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Whisk in @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp},
and @butter{1%tbsp}; cook, whisking occasionally, until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

> If polenta seems too thick, add water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches desired consistency.

Meanwhile, halve and toast @ciabatta bread{1}.

== Serving ==

Cut ciabatta on a diagonal into triangles and drizzle with @olive oil{1%tsp}.

Divide polenta and ragù between shallow bowls in separate sections. Serve
ciabatta on the side.

> Slice chicken crosswise. Serve atop polenta.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.